    // If `a[i] < i`, then `left_len[i]` is `i`.
    // If `a[i] >= i`, then `left_len[i]` is `i+1`.
    // This is simpler: `left_val[i]` is the maximum value `v` such that `v` can be the `i`-th element
    // of an increasing sequence `0, 1, ..., v` where `b_j <= a_j`.
