    //   If `a[0].value + h <= a[n-2].value`, then the max_f is `a[n-2].value + a[n-1].value`.
    //   The min_f is `a[0].value + a[1].value + h`.
    //   The goodness is `(a[n-2].value + a[n-1].value) - (a[0].value + a[1].value + h)`.
    //   This is a candidate for minimal goodness.
